-- Prosecutors say Deutsche Bank's Leithner under investigation
-- By Ludwig Burger
-- Tue Mar 25, 2014 12:48PM EDT
-- None



FRANKFURT, March 25 (Reuters) - Munich Prosecutors said on Tuesday that Deutsche Bank <DBKGn.DE> board member Stephan Leithner is among those under investigation on suspicion of trying to mislead a court in the lender's 12-year legal battle with the heirs of late media mogul Leo Kirch.

The prosecutors conducted a fresh search of Deutsche Bank's headquarters and one private home earlier on Tuesday, targeting employees of Germany's biggest lender as well as lawyers who represented it in the case. [ID:nL5N0MM2R1] Leithner is in charge of human resources, legal and compliance matters as well as government and regulatory affairs at the lender.